
<p><big style="font-size: 130%; font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-variant:small-caps">The</span></big> brain within its groove<br>
Runs evenly and true ;<br>
But let a splinter swerve,<br>
'T were easier for you<br>
To put the water back<br>
When floods have slit the hills,<br>
And scooped a turnpike for themselves,<br>
And blotted out the mills !</p>

<p>The Brain, within its Groove<br>
Runs evenly — and true —<br>
But let a Splinter swerve —<br>
'Twere easier for You —<br><br>
To put a Current back —<br>
When Floods have slit the Hills —<br>
And scooped a Turnpike for Themselves —<br>
And trodden out the Mills —</p>
